<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by the Planning Inspectorate (ESG 30)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.25pt; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:9pt 0pt 0pt 21.25pt; text-align:center; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by the Planning Inspectorate (ESG 30)</span></p><p style="margin:9pt 0pt 0pt 21.25pt; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Summary:</span></p><p style="margin:9pt 0pt 0pt 21.25pt; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In respect of planning applications and appeals, there is an established regulatory regime that addresses planning issues.</span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Despite national policy statements being silent in respect of any explicit reference to shale gas exploration and extraction, a suite of established policy exists that provides decision-makers with a sound and broad range of advice against which applications and appeals can be determined.</span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Other regulator regimes, chiefly operated by NRW and DECC, provide assurance that any operations are conducted safely and properly. The planning system should not seek to duplicate those controls.</span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:9pt 0pt 0pt 21.25pt; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">The Planning Inspectorate (PINs):</span></p><p style="margin:9pt 0pt 0pt 21.25pt; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PINs </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is a Government Agency jointly sponsored by DCLG and Welsh Government dealing with planning appeals and related matters in the two jurisdictions. Other than in respect of Nationally Significant Infrastructure Projects (NSIP) falling within the purview of the Planning Act 2008, the operation of the planning system is devolved to the Welsh Ministers.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Planning policy produced by Welsh Ministers and Local Planning Authorities (LPA) informs appeal decisions made by Planning Inspectors. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">The regulatory regime: planning permission</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Planning permission is required for development comprising </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“the carrying out of building, engineering, mining or other operations in, on, over or under land, or the making of any material change of use in the use of the buildings or other land”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (S.55 TCPA 1990)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Planning applications for development relating to shale gas projects are made to the relevant LPA. As Unitary Authorities, their responsibilities include those of a Mineral Planning Authority.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Applications fall into two distinct categories: those projects relating to plant and operations associated with exploration and testing and secondly, projects associated with any extraction. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The LPA determines whether an Environmental Statement is required under the EIA Regulations 1999 (SI 199 No 293). The Regulations specify two separate lists of projects:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Schedule 1 projects: an EIA is required in every case;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Schedule 2 projects: an EIA is required only if the project is judged likely to give rise to significant environmental effects.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Projects relating to shale gas exploration and/or extraction would be likely to fall within Schedule 2.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In addition to standard consultations including Natural Resources Wales (NRW -successor to the Environment Agency in Wales) in respect of mineral applications, the LPA must notify the Coal Authority if the land contains coal, and/or DECC if it contains gas or oil. (GDPO Art 17, SI 2012/801)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Applications refused planning permission by an LPA, or granted subject to allegedly unacceptable conditions, or where no decision has been made within the appropriate period (see GDPO Art 22 and SI 1999/293) can, within a period of 6 months, be appealed to the Welsh Ministers (S.78 of the TCPA 1990).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Under s.74 of the TCPA, the Welsh Ministers may issue a ‘direction’ restricting the grant of planning permission by an LPA and under s.77 can ‘call-in’ applications for their own determination. Through s.79 Welsh Ministers appoint Planning Inspectors to conduct any inquiry and then to submit a report recommending the suggested outcome. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">The Planning Policy Framework:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">S.38(6) PCA 2004 states “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">If regard is to be had to the development plan for the purpose of any determination to be made under the Planning Acts the determination must be made in accordance with the plan unless material considerations indicate otherwise”.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The development plan comprises adopted Structure Plans, Local Plans, Unitary Development Plans and Minerals Plans unless and until those Plans are superseded by Local Development Plans (LDP). Currently 10/25 LPAs in Wales have adopted LDPs.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A LDP need not repeat national policy statements issued by Welsh Government. These comprise Planning Policy Wales 2010 (PPW), Minerals Planning Policy Wales 2000 (MPPW) and the associated Technical Advice Notes (TANs). These statements represent material considerations of significant weight.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In respect of oil and gas operations, MPPW states at paragraph 64:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Where oil and gas operations can be carried out in an environmentally acceptable way and consistent with the principles of sustainable development, there is no case in land use planning terms for placing more restrictions on the development than are necessary to ensure the protection of the environment. Development plans should indicate those areas where oil and gas operations are likely to be acceptable in principle subject to development control criteria being met in a particular case, as well as those areas where operations are unlikely to be acceptable. Policies should distinguish clearly between the three stages of exploration, appraisal and development (The Petroleum Act 1998). Mineral planning authorities should establish with the Department of Trade and Industry (now DECC) the areas which are licensed, and identify any environmental and other constraints on production and processing in those </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">areas. The industry has an important role to play in making available to authorities information on their forward plans and the extent of known resources. The licence system (The Coal Act 1994) brought into effect in 1995 introduced a single licence, the Petroleum Exploration and Development Licence (PEDL) covering exploration, appraisal and developmental activity. Activities under such licences must be carried out in accordance with the requirements for planning permission. For coalbed methane, permission will be required also from the owner of the coal, usually the Coal Authority. It should be noted that off-shore oil and gas production is likely to require onshore installations that may require planning permission.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">MPPW also states in respect of:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 162pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-108pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">(a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Para 21: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">National Parks and AONB</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:- “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Minerals development should not take place in these areas save in exceptional circumstances…..”.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 148.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-99pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">(b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Para 23:  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Special Protection Areas; Special Areas of Conservation and Ramsar sites</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:- “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Minerals proposals within or likely to significantly affect potential and classified SPAs, designated, candidate or proposed SACs or Ramsar sites must be carefully examined in relation to the site’s conservation objectives in order to ascertain whether or not they are likely to be significant in terms of the ecological objectives of the site”.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 153pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-99pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">(c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Para 25 :  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">SSSIs and National Nature Reserves</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:- “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Minerals proposals within SSSIs or likely to affect them should be very carefully </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 155.95pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">considered, and where the impact is likely to be significant they should be subject to the most rigorous examination, and the need for the mineral must be balanced against environmental and other relevant considerations”.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Planning Policy Wales (PPW) also states in respect of such sensitive areas:-</span></p><p style="margin:9pt 0pt 0pt 155.95pt; text-indent:-63.8pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Para 5.5.6: “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">In National Parks or AONBs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">, special considerations apply to major development proposals which are more national than local in character. Major developments should not take place in National Parks or AONBs except in exceptional circumstances. This may arise where, after rigorous examination, there is demonstrated to be an overriding public need and refusal would be severely detrimental to the local economy and there is no potential for locating the development elsewhere or meeting the need in some other way.</span></p><p style="margin:9pt 0pt 0pt 155.95pt; text-indent:-63.8pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.4pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PPW states that the effects of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">pollution</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> on human health and the environment is relevant (Para 12.1.5); that planning and environmental management are separate but complementary and do not duplicate one another (Para 13.1.1); LPAs and NRW should thus work together to avoid or minimise risks (Para 12.7.2); </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Planning authorities should operate on the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">basis that the relevant pollutant control regimes will be properly applied and enforced by other agencies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (13.10.2). </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 155.95pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-134.65pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.4pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">PPW and TAN 15 also provide a sequential, risk based approach to ensure that development is located away from areas at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">risk of flooding</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> whenever possible. Risk assessments are often required to inform decisions and any requirements for mitigation measures. Likewise, PPW and TAN 5 provide policy guidance in respect </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">of nature conservation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and TAN 11 in relation to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">noise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:22pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Appeals in Wales:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There have been no planning appeals in respect of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">extraction</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of gas from shale beds in Wales. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Two appeals have been allowed subject to conditions relating to operating hours and noise emissions and detailed matters in respect of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">exploration/testing boreholes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in 2010 and 2012:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(a)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Wrexham (A/10/2122444): Main issues = the effects of traffic, noise and disturbance on local residents. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(b)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Vale of Glamorgan (A/11/2167112): Main issues = the effects upon the quantity and quality of groundwater supplies in the area. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Other principal issues that may be material to the determination of similar applications and appeals include:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 108pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">dust and air quality;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 108pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">lighting and visual intrusion and impact upon an area’s character and appearance;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 108pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">impact upon the local setting especially in sensitive areas or where sensitive features exist – e.g. listed buildings, ancient monuments, world heritage sites etc)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 108pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">impact upon nature conservation</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 108pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(e)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">risk through contamination to land or soil resources</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 108pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(f)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">impact upon agricultural land especially that of high quality</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 108pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(g)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">impact upon flood risk</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 108pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(h)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">impact of any land subsidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 108pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(i)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mitigation, restoration, aftercare measures</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:22pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Conclusions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> :</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 26.95pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As set out in the Summary </span></p><p style="margin:9pt 0pt 0pt 21.25pt; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:9pt 0pt 0pt 21.25pt; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.25pt; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>